{"title_page": "Jan Jelinek", "text_new": "{{About|the German musician|the Czech footballer|Jan Jel\u00ednek}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n|name = Jan Jelinek\n|image = Jan jelinek serie4 4.jpg\n|caption =\n|background = non_vocal_instrumentalist\n|alias = The Exposures<br/>Farben<br/>Gramm<br/>N. Gratin\n|origin = [[Berlin]], [[Germany]]\n|instrument =\n|genre = [[Minimal techno]], [[glitch (music)|glitch]], [[microhouse]], [[Ambient music|ambient]], [[Intelligent dance music|IDM]]\n|occupation = Producer, musician\n|years_active = 1998\u2013present\n|label = [[~scape]], [[En/Of]], [[Soup Disk]], [[Audiosphere]], [[Faitiche]]\n|associated_acts =\n|website = [http://www.janjelinek.com/ www.janjelinek.com]\n}}\n\n'''Jan Jelinek''' is a German [[electronic music]]ian who also operates under the names '''Farben''', '''Gramm''' and '''The Exposures'''.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Jan Jelinek {{!}} Biography & History {{!}} AllMusic|url = http://www.allmusic.com/artist/jan-jelinek-mn0000177310/biography|website = AllMusic|accessdate = 2015-09-23|last = Potts|first = Diana}}</ref> His music is usually categorized as [[minimal techno]], [[glitch (music)|glitch]] or [[microhouse]], and is characterized by deep [[bassline]]s, extensive use of [[Sampling (music)|samples]] from earlier [[jazz]] and [[Rock music|rock]] recordings,<ref>{{Cite web|title = RA: Jan Jelinek|url = http://www.residentadvisor.net/dj/janjelinek/biography|website = Resident Advisor|accessdate = 2015-09-23}}</ref> and [[glitch (music)|clicks & cuts]] effects. He is the founder of the German record label Faitiche.<ref>{{Cite web|title = Faitiche - What is faitiche?|url = http://faitiche.de/index.php?article_id=6|website = faitiche.de|accessdate = 2015-09-23|archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20160208153855/http://faitiche.de/index.php?article_id=6|archive-date = 8 February 2016|url-status = dead}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://eventseeker.com/artist/40192-jan-jelinek|title=Jan Jelinek - Artist Profile|